oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cedarcrest Jamboree - 12-27 - WSM - part 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two excerpts of Cedarcrest shoes sponsored radio program Cedarcrest Jamboree, orginally broadcast December 27 and January 3, year unknown, as stated on cue sheet and label, part 2 of each segment. Featuring Louis Buck (announcer), Carl Smith (host ,announcer), Little Jimmy Dickens (performer), Mac Wiseman (performer), Grady Martin (performer), and Grandpa Jones (performer) on radio station WSM (Nashville, Tenn.)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Little Jimmy Dickens; Mac Wiseman; Carl Smith; Grady Martin; Grandpa Jones
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Test tones -- Carl Smith talks about Little Jimmy Dickens performance and introduces Mac Wiseman -- Mac Wiseman talks about Cedarcrest shoes -- Fire In My Heart (Mac Wiseman) -- Carl Smith introduces the next song -- Lily Of The Valley (Carl Smith) -- Carl Smith introduces Mac Wiseman -- I'll Still Write Your Name In The Sand (Mac Wiseman) -- Carl Smith talks introduces Grady Martin -- Dance All Night (Grady Martin fiddle) -- Closing statement (Carl Smith and Louis Buck) -- Closing theme -- Carl Smith introduces Little Jimmy Dickens -- Little Jimmy Dickens tells jokes -- You Don't Have Love At All (Little Jimmy Dickens) -- Carl Smith talks about Dickens performance and introduces Grandpa Jones -- It's Raining Here This Morning (Grandpa Jones) -- Carl Smith introduces the next song -- If We Never Meet Again This Side Of Heaven (Carl Smith) -- Carl Smith introduces Grandpa Jones -- Bald Headed End Of The Broom (Grandpa Jones) -- Carl Smith introduces Grady Martin -- Tennessee Wagner (Grady Martin fiddle) -- Closing statement (Carl Smith and Louis Buck) -- Closing theme -- Cedarcrest shoes commercial (Louis Buck)
